# Code owners for the Decepticon repository.
#
# Strategy: per-path code-owner review, NOT a blanket `* @owner` rule.
# Day-to-day PRs (agents/tools/skills/tests/docs) self-merge once CI
# is green. Supply-chain critical paths below require owner review.
#
# Docs: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-security/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners

# CI / workflow / actions — supply-chain blast radius
.github/workflows/**             @PurpleCHOIms
.github/actions/**               @PurpleCHOIms
.github/CODEOWNERS               @PurpleCHOIms

# Package metadata & versioning — controls what ends up on PyPI/GHCR
pyproject.toml                   @PurpleCHOIms
packages/*/pyproject.toml        @PurpleCHOIms
uv.lock                          @PurpleCHOIms
clients/cli/package.json         @PurpleCHOIms
clients/web/package.json         @PurpleCHOIms
package-lock.json                @PurpleCHOIms
clients/launcher/go.mod          @PurpleCHOIms
clients/launcher/go.sum          @PurpleCHOIms
clients/launcher/.goreleaser.yaml @PurpleCHOIms

# Plugin contracts — public API surface for downstream plugin authors
packages/decepticon-core/decepticon_core/contracts/**    @PurpleCHOIms
packages/decepticon-core/decepticon_core/protocols/**    @PurpleCHOIms
packages/decepticon-core/decepticon_core/registry/**     @PurpleCHOIms

# Install / bootstrap path — runs as user, root, or sudo on user machines
scripts/install.sh               @PurpleCHOIms

# Docker base images / compose entrypoints — change blast radius is the
# whole running stack for every OSS user
docker-compose.yml               @PurpleCHOIms
containers/*.Dockerfile          @PurpleCHOIms
